messages.text: Did you leave something on the sofa before you went on your trip?
Jenna plops into an airport lounge seat, her pulse pattering.
What do you mean?
I found this cute little rubber thing that‚Äôs connected to a battery.

OMG.
Imagine my surprise‚Ä¶
When I came back from my trip to find this special gift from my roomie waiting for me!
What‚Äôs it for anyway?
Stop teasing!!!
You know damned well what it‚Äôs for.
Can you just put it away and forget this happened?
But I have so many questions‚Ä¶
When do you use this? How often?
Adam‚Ä¶
And who do you think about when you use it?
Ok. No more teasing. Purged from my mind.
Who do you think I‚Äôm thinking about?

Were you really?
Yeah‚Ä¶
Sorry. I shouldn‚Äôt have joked.
I know the fastest way to alienate a roomie is to do exactly that.
But what if that roomie is constantly out of town when you‚Äôre out of town?
What if you don‚Äôt see him?
And what if he‚Äôs moving out after his condo is refurbished in a little over a week?

The same kind of thing I would have said to you a few years ago in college.
You mercilessly teased me then too.
Usually about when I‚Äôd get a boyfriend.
That‚Äôs because you never seemed interested in anything but math.
I was trying to get you out of your shell.
Jenna‚Äôs skin flushes.
Hey would you look at that‚Äîmy plane is boarding.
Don‚Äôt dodge this.
You need to explain that comment you made.

No one.
Jen‚Ä¶
Jeez, Adam, what do you want me to say?
That I‚Äôm thinking of YOU?
Why not me?
Because you‚Äôre‚Ä¶you! And I‚Äôm me!

It means we‚Äôre coworkers who share a living space for now.
You‚Äôre a former frat boy and I‚Äôm the nerd who tutored you.
All I hear are excuses.
Huh?
You can‚Äôt tell me you‚Äôve never walked by my room and thought about me.
Because I‚Äôve done that with you.
Jenna nearly drops the phone.
Last week you came home from a trip and went to sleep just as I was getting out of bed.
I imagined your gorgeous black hair spread over the pillow.
I thought about what you might be wearing and hoped you didn‚Äôt have on anything at all.
STOP teasing me. Guys like you don‚Äôt‚Ä¶you know.
What?
You‚Äôve got a lot of women to choose from, all right?

You really have no idea, do you?
I can‚Äôt believe we‚Äôre having this conversation.

Another minute drags by.
You don‚Äôt!
Listen‚Äîwhat if I made you a promise?
What?
That if you let me talk to you like this‚Ä¶
Then if we run into each other in your place, none of this will ever come up.
Our schedules don‚Äôt allow us to be home at the same time to interact anyway, but still.

Because I‚Äôm SO up for that.
That‚Äôs not what I‚Äôm proposing at all.
I want you to tell me all about last night.
Jenna peers around her in the crowded lounge as boarding starts.
Why should I do that?
Because I want to see this side of you.
And we‚Äôre halfway across the country from each other, so there‚Äôs nothing to lose.
Jenna smiles as heat consumes her, years of fantasies rushing her.
üòà
She blows out a breath.

DON‚ÄôT YOU DARE!
